====P2P Foundation Partners====
The [[P2P Foundation:About | P2P Foundation]] works with a number of organizations and individuals to fulfill our mission to connect individuals and groups with each other and to publicize and provide the opportunity to reflect on and better understand the emergence and proliferation of Peer-to-Peer Alternatives.  Some of our partners are listed on this page with links to their respective articles on this wiki.

====Partnering with the P2p Foundation====
Currently the bulk of the partnerships we enjoy are informal.  As the space for network partnerships evolves into something where more formal collaboration is taking place additional partnership categories are developed.  In the meantime partnerships are described on the pages of each partner below.

